---
title: Music Recommender — Music Theory — Sequence Diagram
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor User
    participant GK as Gatekeeper
    participant OAI as OpenAI Moderation
    participant CASS_IN as Cass (Input)
    participant Misty
    participant LFM as Last.fm
    participant RB as Radio Browser
    participant Tempo
    participant Prestige
    participant ANT as Anthropic API
    participant Hertz
    participant Maestro
    participant CASS_OUT as Cass (Output)
    participant LOG as logs/session.log

    User->>GK: TasteProfile (name, context, tags)

    Note over GK: Normalize input:<br/>strip control chars · decode base64<br/>collapse homoglyphs · expand leetspeak<br/>reject RTL overrides

    GK->>OAI: normalized text fields
    OAI-->>GK: moderation verdict

    alt Input flagged
        GK-->>User: plain-language refusal panel
        GK->>LOG: log attempt (profile name only)
        Note over GK: Exit cleanly — graph never starts
    else API unavailable
        GK-->>User: safety check unavailable — retry
        GK->>LOG: log moderation API failure
        Note over GK: Fail closed — exit cleanly
    else Input cleared
        GK->>CASS_IN: TasteProfile (cleared)
    end

    CASS_IN->>LOG: session start (profile name · timestamp)
    CASS_IN->>Misty: TasteProfile

    Note over Misty: ThreadPoolExecutor — both sources called simultaneously

    par Last.fm retrieval
        Misty->>LFM: tag.gettoptracks (per tag)
        LFM-->>Misty: track list
        Misty->>LFM: track.gettoptags (per track)
        LFM-->>Misty: tag list per track
    and Radio Browser retrieval
        Misty->>RB: stations/search (per tag · sorted by votes)
        RB-->>Misty: station list
    end

    Note over Misty: Filter both catalogs against TAG_BLOCKLIST<br/>Remove adult/explicit Radio Browser stations<br/>Require min 10 votes on Radio Browser stations

    Misty->>LOG: retrieval counts (lastfm N · radio N)
    Misty->>Tempo: merged raw_catalog (AgentState)

    Note over Tempo: No LLM — pure numpy cosine similarity<br/>profile_vec · song_vec → similarity_score + vector_breakdown

    Tempo->>Misty: scored_songs (ranked, vector_breakdown per song)

    Note over Tempo: Writes scored_songs to AgentState

    Tempo->>Prestige: top 10 scored_songs (AgentState)

    loop For each of top 10 songs
        Prestige->>ANT: Glass Box prompt (claude-sonnet-4-6)<br/>scoring evidence + user_input delimiters
        ANT-->>Prestige: submit_glass_box_explanation tool call<br/>{explanation, confidence}
    end

    Prestige->>LOG: explanation count · avg confidence
    Prestige->>Hertz: explained_songs (AgentState)

    Hertz->>ANT: quality evaluation (claude-haiku-4-5)<br/>explained_songs list + user_input delimiters
    ANT-->>Hertz: submit_critique tool call<br/>{approved, confidence, reason}

    Hertz->>LOG: confidence · approved · loop_back decision

    alt confidence < 0.7 AND loop_count < 3
        Note over Hertz: loop_back = True · increment loop_count
        Hertz->>Misty: loop back — retrieve fresh catalog
    else approved OR loop_count >= 3
        Note over Hertz: loop_back = False<br/>ceiling reached → deliver best available
        Hertz->>Maestro: explained_songs (AgentState)
    end

    Maestro->>ANT: trajectory selection (claude-haiku-4-5)<br/>candidate list + user_input delimiters
    ANT-->>Maestro: submit_final_trajectory tool call<br/>{selected_indices[5], trajectory_note}

    Note over Maestro: Validate indices · deduplicate<br/>Fall back to confidence order if indices invalid

    Maestro->>LOG: final trajectory · song count · trajectory note
    Maestro->>CASS_OUT: final_trajectory (AgentState)

    Note over CASS_OUT: Render each ExplainedSong as Rich panel:<br/>title · artist · source · Glass Box explanation<br/>similarity score · vector breakdown · tag overlap · URL

    CASS_OUT-->>User: 5-song trajectory with Glass Box explanations
    CASS_OUT->>LOG: session end (songs · confidence · loop_count)
